a) Inheritance is a concept used in object oriented programming where a subclass or child class inherits the attributes of the super class.
for example a baby inheriting the characteristics  of her parents such as color, height.

b) Encapsulation  is where attributes of a class are protected from unauthorized access.


c)Polymorphism comes from poly which means "many" morphism which means "forms"


d)Object is an instance of a class. For example Fruit is a class and apple is an object.

c)A constructor is used to initialize the parameters of a class.
